Saco voters on Tuesday elected former Mayor William Doyle as the next Ward 3 City Councilor. 

Doyle received 69 votes, while political newcomer Robert Henry got 66, according to unofficial results shared by City Clerk Michele Hughes.

Write-in candidates received 9 votes. Saco resident Jay Andrews had said on social media Jan. 1 that he was seeking the seat as a write-in.

The seat became available in October when former Councilor Joseph Gunn resigned after moving out of Ward 3, which encompasses much of the northern part of the city near Route 1. 

