The final unofficial turnout was 144 votes cast.

Henry, a reverend and first-time candidate, spent all day Tuesday at the polls, greeting Saco residents at the door.

“To me, it’s cool because it’s my first time,” he said. “I think people are leaving believing they’ve done something.”

Saco resident Paul Shaw said he voted in Tuesday’s election because it was important.

“Not too many people show up for off-year local elections, but they’re important because they’re the ones that will affect us the most,” Shaw said.

